com.ibm.is.cc.javastage.api

Class PropertyDefinition

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.is.cc.javastage.api.PropertyDefinition

  • public class PropertyDefinition
extends Object
    This PropertyDefinition class represents the definition of a a user-defined property that is required to run the user's Java code. At job design time, Java Integration stage stage editor will call Processor.getUserPropertyDefinitions() to get a list of user-defined property definitions and then show the editor panel to allow the users to specify the String value for each property. The following example shows how to specify a list of user-defined property definition. 

     public List getUserPropertyDefinitions()
 {
    List list = new ArrayList();
    list.add(new PropertyDefinition("dbname", 
                                    "", 
                                    "Database", 
                                    "Specifies the name of the database to connect to.",
                                    PropertyDefinition.Scope.STAGE)); 
    list.add(new PropertyDefinition("table", 
                                    "", 
                                    "Table", 
                                    "Specifies the name of the table to connect to.", 
                                    PropertyDefinition.Scope.LINK)); 
    return list;
 }

    The name and its value will be saved as Java Integration stage property. At runtime, the user's Java code can retrieve a set of = pair by calling the Configuration.getUserProperties() for stage properties,

    Properties props = config.getUserProperties(); String databaseName = props.getProperty("dbname");

    and Link.getUserProperties() for link properties.

    Properties props = link.getUserProperties(); String tableName = props.getProperty("table");

    Version:
    1.0
    See Also:
    Processor.getUserPropertyDefinitions(), Configuration.getUserProperties(), Link.getUserProperties()
